WISE WORDS FROM...Thomas Kochan

"I think [the idea that we will all become free agents] is overstated.
We depend on installed knowledge in our workplaces to keep our
organizations functioning. If we all became free agents, I'm afraid
we would not only have a less productive society, but also a reasonably
unpleasant society as well."  

MIT's Thomas Kochan is a leading academic in the field of Industrial
Relations. Last week we talked about social contracts, this week we
discuss the legal and social climate.

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1011861003

*****************************************************************

ARTICLES TO HELP YOU

Mark Gorkin has the dubious pleasure of consulting on stress to
the US Post Office. He talks about the dynamics that trigger
workplace violence in this first part of a series on Going Postal.

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1011881003

Years ago I learned that assessment tests were unreliable. John
Towler brings me up-to-date with his short article, Do Assessment
Tests Work?

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1011891003

This week we have Research Briefs on international views of
appropriate sexual behavior and on the falling legitimacy of unions.

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1011901003

"Do you know what it means to go to an office where you are
respected as a human being; where your opinion is appreciated;
where your superiors treat you as an equal? It means you've gone
to the wrong office." - Author unknown
See Dr. William Denney's Guest editorial inspired by this wisdom. 

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1011911003

Don't miss the week's Biz Fiction and your Horoscope.

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1011921003

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1012141003


